cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper discusses the optimization of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) as base stations in next-generation wireless networks. This topic falls under the category of computer networks and the sub-category of network architecture and design (cs.NI). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could fall under the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of UAVs as base stations also involves control systems (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO) as the UAVs need to be controlled and maneuvered.
